## Bug

**Target**
EFM32GG

**Toolchain:**
GCC_ARM

**Toolchain version:**
6.x

**mbed-os sha:**
`4978a08ae274`

** Code **

```
#include "mbed.h"

DigitalOut led1(LED1);

// main() runs in its own thread in the OS
int main() {
    while (true) {
        led1 = !led1;
        wait(0.5);
    }
}
```

**Expected behavior**
LED is blinking for all the build profiles.

**Actual behavior**
LED stays on for develop and release and blinks for debug.

**Details**
The issue is around sleep, for develop and release profiles the platforms calls sleep inside the idle handler: https://github.com/ARMmbed/mbed-os/blob/master/rtos/rtos_idle.c#L26 for debug it's disabled.

The EFM32 hal_sleep call looks like that:
```
void hal_sleep(void)
{
    if (sleep_block_counter[0] > 0) {
        /* Blocked everything below EM0, so just return */
        return;
    } else if (sleep_block_counter[1] > 0) {
        /* Blocked everything below EM1, enter EM1 */
        EMU_EnterEM1();
    } else if (sleep_block_counter[2] > 0) {
        /* Blocked everything below EM2, enter EM2 */
        EMU_EnterEM2(true);
    } else {
        /* Blocked everything below EM3, enter EM3 */
        EMU_EnterEM3(true);
    } /* Never enter EM4, as mbed has no way of configuring EM4 wakeup */
    return;
}
```
it seems that the board goes into a too deep sleep and cannot wake up on the systick. When I modify the sleep function to only call `EMU_EnterEM1();` everything works fine.

